   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "\n",
    "pd.set_option('display.max_rows', 100)\n",
    "pd.set_option('display.max_columns', 100)\n",
    "from sklearn.datasets import make_classification\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import PrecisionRecallDisplay, RocCurveDisplay\n",
    "from sklearn.dummy import DummyClassifier\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import average_precision_score\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import precision_recall_curve\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import roc_auc_score\n",
    "from sklearn.svm import LinearSVC\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2a09561d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Part 1. SVM, LR, and Probability Calibration (2 points + 0.5 bonus)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a8196735",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### **Task 1.1 Comparing methods** (0.5 points)\n",
    "\n",
    "Let us generate synthetic data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "8607950f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# fix random_state for reproducibility\n",
    "X, y = make_classification(\n",
    "    n_samples=10000, n_features=10, n_informative=5, n_redundant=5, random_state=42\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.3, random_state=42)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6b111111",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### **Random classifier**\n",
    "\n",
    "First, let us define the simplest possible model, which outputs a random answer for each object. Using the test set, compute AUC-ROC and AUC-PR."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "04c12894",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "random_classifier = DummyClassifier(strategy='uniform', random_state=42).fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
    "y_random = random_classifier.predict_proba(X_test)[:,1]\n",
    "y_random"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "23e027b0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Question:** we are solving a binary classification problem, but `y_random` contains some fractional values rather than 0/1. Why?\n",
    "\n",
    "**Answer:** `predict_proba` returns *class probabilities*, not hard class labels. The `DummyClassifier` with `strategy='uniform'` randomly draws a class with equal probability for each sample; internally sklearn estimates these probabilities from the training class distribution, yielding 0.5 for a balanced dataset. These are probability estimates, so they naturally live in [0, 1] rather than {0, 1}."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "84734039",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def depict_pr_roc(y_true, y_pred, classifier_name='Some Classifier', ax=None):\n",
    "    if ax is None:\n",
    "        fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(11, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(classifier_name, 'metrics')\n",
    "    PrecisionRecallDisplay.from_predictions(y_true, y_pred, ax=ax[0], name=classifier_name)\n",
    "    print('AUC-PR: %.4f' % average_precision_score(y_true, y_pred))\n",
    "    ax[0].set_title(\"PRC\")\n",
    "    ax[0].set_ylim(0, 1.1)\n",
    "\n",
    "    RocCurveDisplay.from_predictions(y_true, y_pred, ax=ax[1], name=classifier_name)\n",
    "    print('AUC-ROC: %.4f' % roc_auc_score(y_true, y_pred))\n",
    "    ax[1].set_title(\"ROC\")\n",
    "    ax[1].set_ylim(0, 1.1)\n",
    "\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "depict_pr_roc(y_test, y_random, 'Random Classifier')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "11111111",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### **Support Vector Machine (Linear Kernel)**\n",
    "\n",
    "Train a support vector machine. Tune the regularization parameter `C` using AUC-PR as the criterion."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "svm_train",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import MinMaxScaler\n",
    "\n",
    "# Tune C via cross-validation on training set\n",
    "C_values = [0.001, 0.01, 0.1, 1, 10, 100]\n",
    "best_C_svm, best_score_svm = None, -np.inf\n",
    "\n",
    "for C in C_values:\n",
    "    svm = LinearSVC(C=C, max_iter=5000, random_state=42)\n",
    "    # Use decision_function scores; cross_val_score with average_precision needs predict_proba\n",
    "    # We use roc_auc as proxy since LinearSVC has no predict_proba\n",
    "    scores = cross_val_score(svm, X_train, y_train, cv=5, scoring='average_precision')\n",
    "    mean_score = scores.mean()\n",
    "    print(f'C={C:.4f}  AUC-PR={mean_score:.4f}')\n",
    "    if mean_score > best_score_svm:\n",
    "        best_score_svm = mean_score\n",
    "        best_C_svm = C\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'\\nBest C for SVM: {best_C_svm}')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Train the final SVM\n",
    "svm_model = LinearSVC(C=best_C_svm, max_iter=5000, random_state=42)\n",
    "svm_model.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
    "\n",
    "# SVM does not produce probabilities; use decision_function scores and scale to [0,1]\n",
    "svm_scores = svm_model.decision_function(X_test)\n",
    "# Normalize to [0, 1] for plotting alongside probabilities\n",
    "svm_scores_norm = (svm_scores - svm_scores.min()) / (svm_scores.max() - svm_scores.min())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "svm_analyze",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "On the test set: plot the ROC and PR curves, compute AUC-ROC and AUC-PR.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Curve analysis:**\n",
    "- As the threshold **increases**, precision generally rises (we only predict positive for very high-confidence samples) while recall falls (we miss more true positives). On the ROC curve, a higher threshold moves toward the bottom-left (fewer predicted positives → lower TPR and lower FPR).\n",
    "- The curves are **not strictly monotonic** because multiple thresholds may give the same precision/recall pair (ties in scores), producing flat segments, and at very high thresholds very few predictions are made which can cause precision to fluctuate."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "svm_plot",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 5))\n",
    "depict_pr_roc(y_test, svm_scores_norm, 'SVM (LinearSVC)', ax=ax)\n",
    "plt.suptitle('SVM Test Set Performance')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print('\\n--- Comparison with Random Classifier ---')\n",
    "print(f'Random  AUC-PR: {average_precision_score(y_test, y_random):.4f}  |  AUC-ROC: {roc_auc_score(y_test, y_random):.4f}')\n",
    "print(f'SVM     AUC-PR: {average_precision_score(y_test, svm_scores_norm):.4f}  |  AUC-ROC: {roc_auc_score(y_test, svm_scores_norm):.4f}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "lr_intro",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### **Logistic Regression**\n",
    "\n",
    "Do the analogous task for logistic regression with L2 regularization: tune `C`, plot curves, report metrics, and compare all 3 classifiers on the same figure."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "lr_train",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Tune C for Logistic Regression\n",
    "best_C_lr, best_score_lr = None, -np.inf\n",
    "\n",
    "for C in C_values:\n",
    "    lr = LogisticRegression(C=C, max_iter=1000, random_state=42)\n",
    "    scores = cross_val_score(lr, X_train, y_train, cv=5, scoring='average_precision')\n",
    "    mean_score = scores.mean()\n",
    "    print(f'C={C:.4f}  AUC-PR={mean_score:.4f}')\n",
    "    if mean_score > best_score_lr:\n",
    "        best_score_lr = mean_score\n",
    "        best_C_lr = C\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'\\nBest C for LR: {best_C_lr}')\n",
    "\n",
    "lr_model = LogisticRegression(C=best_C_lr, max_iter=1000, random_state=42)\n",
    "lr_model.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
    "y_lr = lr_model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]\n",
    "\n",
    "# All 3 classifiers on the same figure\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(13, 5))\n",
    "depict_pr_roc(y_test, y_random, 'Random Classifier', ax=ax)\n",
    "depict_pr_roc(y_test, svm_scores_norm, 'SVM', ax=ax)\n",
    "depict_pr_roc(y_test, y_lr, 'Logistic Regression', ax=ax)\n",
    "plt.suptitle('All Classifiers Comparison')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print('\\n--- Final Metrics Comparison ---')\n",
    "for name, preds in [('Random', y_random), ('SVM', svm_scores_norm), ('LR', y_lr)]:\n",
    "    print(f'{name:8s}  AUC-PR: {average_precision_score(y_test, preds):.4f}  AUC-ROC: {roc_auc_score(y_test, preds):.4f}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "lr_vs_svm",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Question:** Compare LR and SVM in terms of all quality criteria.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Answer:** Both LR and SVM significantly outperform the random baseline. LR typically has a slight edge in AUC-PR and AUC-ROC on this data because it directly optimises a log-likelihood (probability-based) loss, yielding well-calibrated scores. SVM optimises a margin-based hinge loss and its raw decision-function values are not probabilities, so after the normalisation to [0, 1] some ranking information may be distorted. When the data is linearly separable the gap tends to be small, but on noisy data LR's probabilistic output leads to better-calibrated and often higher-AUC scores."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "task12",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### **Task 1.2. Visualization in SVM and LR approaches** (0.5 points)\n",
    "\n",
    "Generate synthetic data with **2 features**, train SVM, visualise the separating line and support vectors."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "svm_2d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.svm import SVC\n",
    "\n",
    "# 2-feature dataset\n",
    "X2, y2 = make_classification(\n",
