  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "counters_conclusion",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Answer (counters vs OHE):**\n",
    "\n",
    "**Advantages of counters:** (1) Fixed number of output features regardless of cardinality — no feature explosion. (2) Compact, memory-efficient. (3) Can capture target-feature relationship in a single real-valued feature. (4) Works well with high-cardinality features.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Disadvantages of counters:** (1) Introduces target leakage if computed on the full training set — must use cross-fitting or held-out fold. (2) Loses information when multiple categories share similar means. (3) Requires smoothing for rare categories. (4) Not suitable for multi-class targets without additional adjustment."
   ]
  },
