  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "task9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### **Task 9. Embedded methods** (0.5 points)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "embedded",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# --- Without scaling ---\n",
    "start = time.time()\n",
    "lr_emb = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, random_state=42)\n",
    "lr_emb.fit(X_fs_tr, y_fs_tr)\n",
    "top40_idx = np.argsort(np.abs(lr_emb.coef_[0]))[::-1][:K_FEATURES]\n",
    "elapsed_emb = time.time() - start\n",
    "\n",
    "lr_emb2 = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, random_state=42)\n",
    "lr_emb2.fit(X_fs_tr[:, top40_idx], y_fs_tr)\n",
    "pr_emb = average_precision_score(y_adult_te, lr_emb2.predict_proba(X_adult_te_enc[:, top40_idx])[:, 1])\n",
    "print(f'Embedded (no scale)  AUC-PR: {pr_emb:.4f}  Time: {elapsed_emb:.3f}s')\n",
    "\n",
    "# --- With scaling (StandardScaler) ---\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
    "\n",
    "start = time.time()\n",
    "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
    "X_fs_tr_sc = scaler.fit_transform(X_fs_tr)\n",
    "X_fs_val_sc = scaler.transform(X_fs_val)\n",
    "X_te_sc = scaler.transform(X_adult_te_enc)\n",
    "\n",
    "lr_emb_sc = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, random_state=42)\n",
    "lr_emb_sc.fit(X_fs_tr_sc, y_fs_tr)\n",
    "top40_sc = np.argsort(np.abs(lr_emb_sc.coef_[0]))[::-1][:K_FEATURES]\n",
    "elapsed_emb_sc = time.time() - start\n",
    "\n",
    "lr_emb_sc2 = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, random_state=42)\n",
    "lr_emb_sc2.fit(X_fs_tr_sc[:, top40_sc], y_fs_tr)\n",
    "pr_emb_sc = average_precision_score(y_adult_te, lr_emb_sc2.predict_proba(X_te_sc[:, top40_sc])[:, 1])\n",
    "print(f'Embedded (scaled)    AUC-PR: {pr_emb_sc:.4f}  Time: {elapsed_emb_sc:.3f}s')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Did the selected features change?\n",
    "print(f'Feature sets identical: {set(top40_idx) == set(top40_sc)}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "task10",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### **Task 10. Filter Methods** (0.5 points)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Correlation and feature selection:** A higher absolute correlation between a feature and the target indicates a stronger linear relationship, suggesting the feature is more predictive. We select the 40 features with the **highest absolute Pearson correlation** with the target."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "filter",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# --- Correlation filter ---\n",
    "start = time.time()\n",
    "corr = np.abs(np.corrcoef(X_fs_tr.T, y_fs_tr.values)[-1, :-1])\n",
    "top40_corr = np.argsort(corr)[::-1][:K_FEATURES]\n",
    "elapsed_corr = time.time() - start\n",
    "\n",
    "lr_corr = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, random_state=42)\n",
    "lr_corr.fit(X_fs_tr[:, top40_corr], y_fs_tr)\n",
    "pr_corr = average_precision_score(y_adult_te, lr_corr.predict_proba(X_adult_te_enc[:, top40_corr])[:, 1])\n",
    "print(f'Correlation filter  AUC-PR: {pr_corr:.4f}  Time: {elapsed_corr:.4f}s')\n",
    "\n",
    "# --- t-statistic filter ---\n",
    "start = time.time()\n",
    "pos_mask = y_fs_tr.values == 1\n",
    "neg_mask = ~pos_mask\n",
    "\n",
    "mu_pos = X_fs_tr[pos_mask].mean(axis=0)\n",
    "mu_neg = X_fs_tr[neg_mask].mean(axis=0)\n",
    "sigma_pos = X_fs_tr[pos_mask].std(axis=0)\n",
    "sigma_neg = X_fs_tr[neg_mask].std(axis=0)\n",
    "n_pos = pos_mask.sum()\n",
    "n_neg = neg_mask.sum()\n",
    "\n",
    "numerator = np.abs(mu_pos - mu_neg)\n",
    "denominator = np.sqrt((n_pos * sigma_pos**2 + n_neg * sigma_neg**2) / (n_pos + n_neg)) + 1e-12\n",
    "t_stat = numerator / denominator\n",
    "top40_t = np.argsort(t_stat)[::-1][:K_FEATURES]\n",
    "elapsed_t = time.time() - start\n",
    "\n",
    "lr_t = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, random_state=42)\n",
    "lr_t.fit(X_fs_tr[:, top40_t], y_fs_tr)\n",
    "pr_t = average_precision_score(y_adult_te, lr_t.predict_proba(X_adult_te_enc[:, top40_t])[:, 1])\n",
    "print(f't-statistic filter  AUC-PR: {pr_t:.4f}  Time: {elapsed_t:.4f}s')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "task11",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### **Task 11. Wrapper Methods** (1 point)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "wrapper",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def backward_elimination(X_tr, y_tr, X_val, y_val, k=40, step=5):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Greedy backward feature elimination.\"\"\"\n",
    "    remaining = list(range(X_tr.shape[1]))\n",
    "    start = time.time()\n",
    "\n",
    "    while len(remaining) > k:\n",
    "        lr = LogisticRegression(max_iter=500, random_state=42)\n",
    "        lr.fit(X_tr[:, remaining], y_tr)\n",
    "        importances = np.abs(lr.coef_[0])\n",
    "        # number of features to remove this iteration\n",
    "        n_remove = min(step, len(remaining) - k)\n",
    "        # indices of least important features (within `remaining`)\n",
    "        worst_local = np.argsort(importances)[:n_remove]\n",
    "        worst_global = [remaining[i] for i in worst_local]\n",
    "        remaining = [f for f in remaining if f not in worst_global]\n",
    "\n",
    "    elapsed = time.time() - start\n",
    "    return remaining, elapsed\n",
    "\n",
    "selected_wrap, elapsed_wrap = backward_elimination(\n",
    "    X_fs_tr, y_fs_tr, X_fs_val, y_fs_val, k=K_FEATURES, step=10\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "lr_wrap = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, random_state=42)\n",
    "lr_wrap.fit(X_fs_tr[:, selected_wrap], y_fs_tr)\n",
    "pr_wrap = average_precision_score(y_adult_te, lr_wrap.predict_proba(X_adult_te_enc[:, selected_wrap])[:, 1])\n",
    "print(f'Wrapper (backward)  AUC-PR: {pr_wrap:.4f}  Time: {elapsed_wrap:.2f}s')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Summary table\n",
    "print('\\n=== Feature Selection Summary ===')\n",
    "results_fs = {\n",
    "    'Baseline (all)': baseline_pr,\n",
    "    'Embedded (no scale)': pr_emb,\n",
    "    'Embedded (scaled)': pr_emb_sc,\n",
    "    'Filter (correlation)': pr_corr,\n",
    "    'Filter (t-stat)': pr_t,\n",
    "    'Wrapper (backward)': pr_wrap\n",
    "}\n",
    "for name, pr in results_fs.items():\n",
    "    print(f'{name:30s}  AUC-PR: {pr:.4f}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fs_conclusion",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Feature selection conclusions:**\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Embedded methods**: Fast (done during model training), leverage model's own importance measure. Require scaling for fair comparison. May overfit if features are correlated. *Best when speed is key.*\n",
    "- **Filter methods**: Fastest, model-agnostic, no leakage risk. Correlation ignores interactions; t-statistic is more class-aware. *Best for quick pruning of many features.*\n",
    "- **Wrapper methods**: Most computationally expensive (retrains model at each step), but considers feature interactions. Generally achieves the best quality. *Best when accuracy matters most.*\n",
    "\n",
    "The wrapper typically yields the highest AUC-PR because it evaluates feature subsets rather than individual features."
   ]
  },
